This paper is primarily focused on the fairness of ranked search results, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and APIs, which could also fall under the categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the societal and ethical implications of search rankings, which could fall under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
